        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 17 at 5:47PM MDT by NWS Billings MT</headline>
        <description>At 547 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles north of Hardin, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Hardin and Crow Indian Reservation.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead
to flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
